1
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,250
[CHIO]
On mornings when I can leave

2
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,958
a little earlier than usual,

3
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:44,708
I take a stroll
through the park.

4
00:01:44,791 --> 00:01:47,083
There are so many
interesting people around.

5
00:01:48,250 --> 00:01:49,458
[CHIO]
Hm.

6
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:51,250
--Who parks like that?
--[chattering]

7
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:53,750
Motorcycle gang. Figures.

8
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:56,041
What is there to scream
about at this time of day?

9
00:01:56,125 --> 00:01:58,833
So much for a
peaceful stroll. Gah!

10
00:01:58,916 --> 00:02:01,875
Oh, well. This park's big
enough that I can avoid them.

11
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:04,333
[ANDOU] It was a real deal,
man. I wouldn't lie to ya.

12
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:05,500
[CHIO]
Brain fart.

13
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:06,916
What do I have for
first period again?

14
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,166
[ANDOU]
The name was Bloody Butterfly.

15
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:11,500
No.

16
00:02:11,583 --> 00:02:13,541
[BIKER 3A]
What? Bloody Butterfly?

17
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:14,958
That's not a name, bro.

18
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:16,291
[ANDOU]
Damn straight it is.

19
00:02:16,375 --> 00:02:19,625
It's hers. Had me on the
ground in a single blow.

20
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:22,333
[BIKERS]
Wait. A woman?

21
00:02:22,416 --> 00:02:26,041
[CHIO] Oh, come on!
What's he doing here?!

22
00:02:28,416 --> 00:02:30,500
[ANDOU] That's the reason
I can't stay with you.

23
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:32,041
I promised Bloody Butterfly

24
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:34,333
that I'd give up this life
if she'd let me live.

25
00:02:34,416 --> 00:02:35,250
[BIKER 3A]
And that's it?

26
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,666
[ANDO]
I gave her my word.

27
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,291
[CHIO]
Huh? What the crap?

28
00:02:38,375 --> 00:02:39,625
He took me seriously?

29
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:42,333
How is that even part of
a normal thought process?

30
00:02:42,416 --> 00:02:43,625
[ANDOU]
At first, I thought it was

31
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:45,750
just some psycho
pickin' a fight.

32
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:47,166
But then there she was,

33
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,583
smirking like she just
swallowed my soul.

34
00:02:49,666 --> 00:02:50,833
And that was it.

35
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:53,083
Next thing I know,
I'm trashed on the ground.

36
00:02:53,166 --> 00:02:54,333
That's wicked.

37
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:57,208
But you're the Demon God.
No one scares you.

38
00:02:57,291 --> 00:02:59,666
[BIKER 3B]
No one except Bloody Butterfly!

39
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,625
[BIKER 3C]
Crazy. Why haven't I ever heard

40
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:03,541
of this Bloody Butterfly chick?

41
00:03:03,625 --> 00:03:04,750
[BIKER 3A]
I'll bet Bloody Butterfly

42
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,708
is from some underground turf.

43
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:08,125
[BIKER 3B]
"Bloody Butterfly."

44
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:10,583
Is it 'cause she kills people
with a butterfly knife?

45
00:03:10,666 --> 00:03:12,125
[CHIO]
Stop saying it!

46
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:15,000
It's an online handle that is
meant to be seen, not heard!

47
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:17,458
Of course it sounds stupid
when you say it out loud!

48
00:03:17,541 --> 00:03:20,625
Can I get a pronoun up in here?
Quit repeating it like that!

49
00:03:20,708 --> 00:03:23,000
I can't take it anymore!

50
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:26,125
That's enough. Some things
aren't meant to be understood.

51
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:29,250
Bloody Butterfly is a creature
of the societal underworld.

52
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,958
Have some respect.

53
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:32,416
I learned a lot that day.

54
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,291
After speaking with
Bloody Butterfly,

55
00:03:34,375 --> 00:03:36,833
I finally realized that
we were wasting our lives

56
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:38,333
with this child's play.

57
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:39,875
[screaming]

58
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:43,250
I didn't think it was possible,
but I'm glad to know.

59
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:46,375
Women like Bloody Butterfly
do exist in the world.

60
00:03:46,458 --> 00:03:47,750
[screaming]

61
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,666
Someone so seemingly innocent,

62
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,458
out fighting terrorists,
surviving gang wars...

63
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:55,166
Bloody Butterfly does it all.

64
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:58,041
I'm just impressed that there's
someone who impresses you.

65
00:03:58,125 --> 00:03:59,916
--Shit's wild.
--[BIKER 3D] Bull.

66
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,041
This is way too good to be true!

67
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:04,166
I need to see this
Bloody Butterfly myself!

68
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:05,666
--Take me to her!
--[ANDOU] You dumbass!

69
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,666
Are you saying you
don't trust my word?

70
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:11,208
[CHIO groaning]
This cannot be happening.

71
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:14,000
They need to shut up or
everyone will know who I am!

72
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:17,458
Look, you're the most
badass guy I know.

73
00:04:17,541 --> 00:04:18,625
That's why we gotta meet her.

74
00:04:18,708 --> 00:04:21,083
Even if it means I
drag her here myself.

75
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,541
I'll help.

76
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:25,083
She must know some kind of
underground martial arts BS.

77
00:04:25,166 --> 00:04:27,916
Otherwise, how would
anyone beat you?

78
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,500
[BIKER 3D]
Then it's settled!

79
00:04:29,583 --> 00:04:31,541
We do everything in our power
to find her and learn her trade!

80
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:34,625
[ALL] Let the hunt for
Bloody Butterfly begin!

81
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:39,208
[BIKER 3D]
What's the matter? Are you okay?

82
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:42,791
Don't move! Don't say
a word. Don't breathe.

83
00:04:42,875 --> 00:04:44,458
Don't turn around.

84
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:52,791
Um... How the...
Where'd you come from?

85
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,875
Bloody Butterfly?

86
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:59,458
[BIKERS]
What? Oh, no!

87
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:03,541
Bloody... Butterfly!

88
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:07,708
Wait. That's Bloody Butterfly?

89
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:11,666
But she's just a kid...
with glasses.

90
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,125
[BIKER 3D] I thought she'd
be all leather suited

91
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:14,666
with blades and shit.

92
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,416
[CHIO sighs] Well, of course
they're gonna be disappointed

93
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,833
after he built me up like that.

94
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:22,916
At least it makes what I have
to say more believable.

95
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,250
You here for me,
Bloody Butterfly?

96
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,833
You guessed it.

97
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:32,000
You and I need to
have a little chat.

98
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:34,791
But not here. I wanna
speak to you alone.

99
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,541
[ANDOU whimpers]

100
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:45,166
[ANDOU] You guys stay put!
I'll be right back.

101
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:46,458
Where are you going?

102
00:05:46,541 --> 00:05:48,208
[ANDOU]
None of your business!

103
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:52,583
'Kay. I'm listening. What is it?

104
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:54,625
I already told you
I'm leaving the gang.

105
00:05:54,708 --> 00:05:56,125
--[ANDOU] I just had to--
--Uh, that's not...

106
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:58,083
[ANDOU gasps]
I get it now.

107
00:05:58,166 --> 00:06:00,583
Right. You're here to
drag me down with you!

108
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:02,750
Sorta...

109
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:06,041
Oh, I'm afraid I may
have misled you somehow.

110
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,875
I've never even held a gun.

111
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:09,791
--Much less killed anyone.
--[CHIO] Yeah, I know! I get it!

112
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:11,416
[ANDOU] I don't think I could
handle the guilt of--

113
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,625
Hey! What I'm
saying is, me, too!

114
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,875
It's all just a big silly lie.

115
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:22,291
[CHIO]
That is a reasonable reaction!

116
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:23,458
So, get this...

117
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:25,125
There's no underground
organization,

118
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:26,458
no killings, no terrorists.

119
00:06:26,541 --> 00:06:28,583
I'm just your average
high school kid.

120
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:31,416
More like, below average.

121
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,625
[chuckles]

122
00:06:32,708 --> 00:06:34,416
[CHIO] No, you can't
laugh! I'm not joking!

123
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,833
I was freaked out after burning
my leg on your muffler thing!

124
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:38,125
Remember when I told
you about guys

125
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:39,541
being crippled for life?

126
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:41,833
I was talking about gamer nerds
being hooked on gaming!

127
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,583
That's "the life"
I was describing!

128
00:06:46,958 --> 00:06:49,250
[CHIO]
The face of disappointment.

129
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,583
But I don't regret
clearing this up.

130
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:52,208
It needed to happen.

131
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:53,958
And I'm glad he
eventually believed me

132
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:56,041
even though believing me is
what got us into this mess

133
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:57,583
in the first place.

134
00:06:57,666 --> 00:07:00,333
Okay. Let's get this straight.

135
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:01,500
[CHIO]
Yes, let's.

136
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:03,666
You're sayin' you're
just a normal kid,

137
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,291
and you were making
your way to school

138
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:08,041
when some hoodlum was
gettin' in your face.

139
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:10,958
You were able to ward him off
with your talent for lying

140
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:12,791
and a little bit of dumb luck.

141
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:15,208
Then you decided to scare
the crap out of him

142
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:16,750
and make him quit his gang.

143
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:19,708
And then this dumb
idiot trusted you.

144
00:07:19,791 --> 00:07:22,208
He went around tellin'
his friends about these lies

145
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:23,333
as if they were true.

146
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:24,583
[screams]

147
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:26,916
And now he looks like
a pathetic joke.

148
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,166
Is that what you just told me?

149
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,166
[CHIO]
Holy crap.

150
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:32,166
He's totally going
to headbutt me!

151
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,833
I can't move!

152
00:07:33,916 --> 00:07:36,291
That's hilarious!

153
00:07:36,375 --> 00:07:37,708
[CHIO]
Huh?

154
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:42,208
[ANDOU laughing]
Frickin' genius.

155
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:44,000
I don't even know what to say.

156
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,000
[laughing]

157
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:48,000
[ANDOU] Oh, man, I hope
they didn't hear me.

158
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,125
This whole damn time,

159
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:51,291
you were just a
normal nerdy kid.

160
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:52,833
Exactly how you look.

161
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:55,958
[laughs] Ridiculous.

162
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:57,333
Man, I guess knowing that

163
00:07:57,416 --> 00:08:00,125
explains why that name
of yours is so lame.

164
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,208
"Bloody Butterfly." [laughs]

165
00:08:02,291 --> 00:08:05,333
I actually said that name
out loud with a straight face!

166
00:08:05,416 --> 00:08:07,791
"Bloody Butterfly." [laughing]

167
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:09,083
Can we not talk about it?

168
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:10,416
The point of this awkward convo

169
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,208
is that I don't want
it to spread anymore.

170
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,875
[ANDOU]
I know, I know!

171
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,875
Well, if I fell for that,

172
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:18,208
I have no regrets
about quitting.

173
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:20,875
Man, you totally got me!

174
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,375
It's their turn.

175
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:25,666
Let's see this through
to the bitter end.

176
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:28,458
Come on. We're headin' back.

177
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:29,875
[CHIO]
"We," as in you and me?

178
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:33,250
[ANDOU] It'll be fun.
Just follow my lead.

179
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:36,125
Should we check on him?
It's been awhile.

180
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,791
[BIKER 3B] Nah, he's fine.
Andou can handle himself.

181
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:41,958
--[ANDOU screaming]
--[ALL gasp]

182
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:43,583
[BIKERS]
What happened?

183
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:45,958
Go! Now! Bloody
Butterfly got me!

184
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:49,375
She's dangerous!
Go save yourselves!

185
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:51,916
Andou, look at me.

186
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,333
Oh, shit!

187
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,750
This is it! She's gonna
kill all of us!

188
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:58,125
She's a monster!

189
00:08:58,208 --> 00:09:00,875
[CHIO]
Slower. Walk slower.

190
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:02,333
She's totally unarmed.

191
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:04,125
She beat his ass
with pure strength!

192
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:06,416
Damn. Looks like
we're all screwed!

193
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:07,791
[ANDOU yelps]
Butterflies!

194
00:09:07,875 --> 00:09:09,083
That's the sign she gives

195
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:11,375
when she's about to use
her special attack!

196
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:12,916
Soon everyone for miles

197
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,250
will be bloodied,
or dead, or something.

198
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:17,166
This is the end!

199
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:20,041
Here she goes! Run!

200
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:22,583
[screaming]

201
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:24,291
You must erase her
from your mind

202
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:26,291
and tell no one of this day!

203
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:28,166
Don't try to provoke her!

204
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:30,083
What are you doing? Run!

205
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:31,541
I will not run!

206
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:34,166
I will end you, Bloody
Butterfly, you hear me?

207
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:37,750
Andou, you're my friend, and
I'm willing to die for you!

208
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:39,500
I told you to run!

209
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:41,416
Go or I'll kill you!

210
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:47,291
[BIKER 3D screaming]

211
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:52,000
[ANDOU]
Well, that should do it.

212
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:54,208
Did ya see the looks
on their faces?

213
00:09:54,291 --> 00:09:55,791
What cowards.

214
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:57,125
Look at this.

215
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:58,875
They call themselves
a biker gang,

216
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,208
and they ran away on foot.

217
00:10:00,291 --> 00:10:03,833
Um, thank you for the adventure!

218
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:05,125
[ANDOU]
Hm?

219
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:08,250
Here. This is for your face.

220
00:10:13,208 --> 00:10:14,541
[ANDOU]
No way.

221
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:17,083
If I take that, things'll
only get more complicated.

222
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:20,208
See ya, Bloody Butterfly!

223
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:23,041
Dude, you have to
stop calling me that!

224
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:25,458
Hey, do you remember that time

225
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:26,958
I told you about
some skanky girl

226
00:10:27,041 --> 00:10:28,666
who came to school
on the back of a bike

227
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:30,166
with a motorcycle gangster?

228
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,666
Uh... I mean, barely.

229
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:34,250
Okay, you're not
allowed to ask how,

230
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,083
but I totally know
who this girl is!

231
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:38,000
I've never seen her around,
but she calls herself

232
00:10:38,083 --> 00:10:39,666
"Bloody Butts and Thighs"
or something.

233
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:42,125
Or maybe it was "Butterfly,"
that sounds familiar.

234
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:43,500
Huh?

235
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:45,875
I'm having gaming flashbacks
for some reason. Hm...

236
00:10:45,958 --> 00:10:47,333
[CHIO]
Um, I used to play you

237
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:49,458
under that name
all the time, dummy.

238
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:51,541
Does it ring any bells for you?

239
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,708
Not even a little bit.

240
00:10:55,125 --> 00:10:57,583
[CHIO] That settles it.
She's the next to go.

241
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:00,833
[CHIO]
<i>Chio's School Road</i> !

242
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:06,333
[CHIO]
He said my handle was lame?

243
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:09,083
Let's see how great
his gang's name is!

244
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:10,500
Found 'em!

245
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:13,916
He didn't even try
to make it intimidating.

246
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,541
It's actually really cute!

247
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:18,750
[CHIO grunting, yelling]

248
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:22,833
Hey, Manana, be a pal and stick
your arm out real quick.

249
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:23,833
Hell no!

250
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:25,208
[CHIO]
Rude!

251
00:11:25,291 --> 00:11:28,333
I wanna see if I'm doing
all my CQC moves correctly.

252
00:11:28,416 --> 00:11:31,083
Oh, okay, let me just
sacrifice my limbs for you.

253
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:33,625
If this is about a video game,
you need an intervention.

254
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:36,166
Man, you don't even know.
That action is awesome!

255
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,916
You wouldn't believe how
good the cut scenes are.

256
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:41,125
Damn, you're really wasting your
life away with that crap, huh?

257
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:42,500
Who hurt you?

258
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:43,583
[CHIO]
Check me out!

259
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:46,208
Face block! Punch!
Roundhouse! Block!

260
00:11:46,291 --> 00:11:47,583
He's comin' from the left.

261
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:48,750
[MANANA] You just look like
you're really determined

262
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,750
to kill flies. It's so...

263
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:55,750
[CHIO]
And... twist!

264
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,750
Give me the password
to the secret pics

265
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:00,500
hidden on your computer,
and the arm lives.

266
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:04,458
Bite me, you're insane!
Just break it!

267
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:06,375
I hope there's some entity
you praise nightly

268
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:07,708
