270
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:12,125
Aw, crap, that reminds me.
Our fitness test is tomorrow.

271
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:13,791
I'm guessing you haven't
prepped for it?

272
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:15,750
Fake it till you make it, bruh.

273
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,458
Chio, you're actually athletic
and in a sports club.

274
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:19,458
It doesn't make sense for you

275
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:21,208
to keep blowing
these things off.

276
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:23,375
Yeah, it does! Once they
know your true skills,

277
00:12:23,458 --> 00:12:25,625
they start forcing you into
sports festivals and tournaments

278
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,333
and I'm not about that!

279
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:30,666
I like being a nobody.
It's peaceful, okay?

280
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,041
I forgot, you're the
patron saint of lame-o's.

281
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:35,541
If some sports star messes up,
the whole country knows.

282
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:37,208
If I mess up, shoulders shrug.

283
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,791
Fine, you wanna work that
fitness, girl? Come on.

284
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:41,791
Let's see how many of these
side squat jumps you can do

285
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:43,125
without looking ridiculous!

286
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:44,500
--Fight me!
--[MANANA] Not yet.

287
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,125
I'd like to go back to
the part where you said

288
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:48,958
"work that fitness" as if
it's your everyday lingo.

289
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,583
Hurry up! Fast as you can!

290
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:53,125
Like some crab waitin'
in line to pee!

291
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:54,750
I dare you to do it faster.

292
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,375
Check it out! Can't even see me!

293
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:58,625
Oh, my god! Do that and say
"kabaddi!" really fast.

294
00:12:58,708 --> 00:13:02,500
--Kabaddi, kabaddi, kabaddi!
--[MANANA laughing]

295
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:05,125
I can't! You look just
like those weirdos!

296
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:06,875
You're even making
the face they make!

297
00:13:06,958 --> 00:13:08,208
I think I broke my ribs!

298
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:10,458
I had no idea you loved kabaddi!

299
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:12,583
--And you know all the moves!
--[CHIO] I didn't even know

300
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:13,833
it was a real thing before...

301
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:16,083
Good morning! Did I hear
you mention kabaddi?

302
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:17,791
Have I got a surprise for you!

303
00:13:17,875 --> 00:13:19,125
[CHIO, MANANA]
Huh? What is it?

304
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:20,708
A kabaddi expert!

305
00:13:20,791 --> 00:13:23,833
[MADOKA]
Hi there. I'm Kushitori Madoka.

306
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:27,583
Captain of the Kabaddi Club.
Nice to meet you both.

307
00:13:27,666 --> 00:13:31,125
[BOTH]
Wait, it's a real club?

308
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:32,375
Shit.

309
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:33,916
[MADOKA] So you wanna
know how to play, huh?

310
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,541
Want to learn all the moves?
That's what it sounded like.

311
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:38,458
Isn't this so exciting?

312
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:41,833
[BOTH] We, uh...
We're sorry about that.

313
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:43,083
But why?

314
00:13:43,166 --> 00:13:44,750
It's not like you were
making fun of it, right?

315
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:45,750
[BOTH]
Right!

316
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:47,000
[MADOKA]
You just admire the sport

317
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:48,666
and were praising the athletes.

318
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:49,916
Uh, yeah.

319
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,375
[MADOKA] You were trying
to figure out the rules

320
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:53,333
so you could play one day.

321
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:54,666
[BOTH]
Yep.

322
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,791
Great! Well, I'm more than
happy to teach you both!

323
00:13:57,875 --> 00:13:59,916
We'll have more room over here.

324
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,458
Isn't this fun?

325
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:04,500
[CHIO] Sure, if FUN
stands for F'd Up Nonsense!

326
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:05,750
Kabaddi, kabaddi, kabaddi,

327
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,708
kabaddi, kabaddi, kabaddi,
kabaddi, kabaddi!

328
00:14:07,791 --> 00:14:09,125
If you're in the
raider position,

329
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:11,500
you keep yelling "kabaddi"
while in the enemy circle.

330
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,125
[CHIO]
Wait, they actually say that?

331
00:14:13,208 --> 00:14:15,333
And here I thought
that was just a joke.

332
00:14:15,416 --> 00:14:17,125
[MADOKA] The object is to
touch your opponents

333
00:14:17,208 --> 00:14:18,666
and run back to your side.

334
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,250
Once on your base,

335
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,375
you get points for everyone you
touched on the opposite team,

336
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,666
and the ones who were touched,
of course, are then out.

337
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:28,625
Got it! So everyone takes
turns being a raider,

338
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:29,958
and whoever isn't a raider

339
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:32,791
has to avoid getting
touched, kinda like tag?

340
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:33,875
[MADOKA]
Correct.

341
00:14:33,958 --> 00:14:35,916
[CHIO]
Wow, I so totally don't care!

342
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,291
How is this my life?

343
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:39,541
"Sorry I'm late. I was
forced into kabaddi lessons

344
00:14:39,625 --> 00:14:40,833
against my will!"

345
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:44,000
I wish she'd just let us go!
I got stuff to do!

346
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:45,208
[MADOKA]
The biggest difference, though,

347
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:48,166
is the defense has
a way of scoring, too.

348
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,500
If you're on defense,

349
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:51,458
try to tackle and capture
the raider like this.

350
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,291
Your team gets the point
if you completely stop

351
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:55,208
their movement in their tracks.

352
00:14:55,291 --> 00:14:56,916
It sounds like a lot,
but just remember:

353
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,916
raiders touch, defense catches.

354
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,375
Well, I sure learned
a lot today!

355
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:01,875
Me, too! This was great!

356
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:04,583
Good to hear! Now let's play!

357
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:07,833
If you lose, you join
the club. Deal?

358
00:15:07,916 --> 00:15:09,541
Sweet! That'll help us out

359
00:15:09,625 --> 00:15:11,041
'cause, once all the
third years graduate,

360
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:12,958
the club will be
short on members.

361
00:15:13,041 --> 00:15:14,791
You have no idea
how stoked I was

362
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:17,333
when I heard some first years
were so interested in the game!

363
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:18,791
Well, define "interested."

364
00:15:18,875 --> 00:15:20,375
--Unless...
--[CHIO] So close.

365
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,041
...there's been
a misunderstanding.

366
00:15:22,125 --> 00:15:24,083
I asked before if you were
making fun of my sport

367
00:15:24,166 --> 00:15:26,875
and you said no.
Is that still true?

368
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:28,083
[CHIO]
I get it.

369
00:15:28,166 --> 00:15:29,708
This was revenge
by guilt-splaining.

370
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:32,458
She wants to prove
it's not a joke sport.

371
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:34,958
Ugh! If she wasn't a
third year, I'd be out.

372
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:37,666
But I can't risk being
noticed by haters.

373
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:40,416
Fine. Let's hurry
and get it over with.

374
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,541
All right, you two
are the raiders!

375
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:43,958
I chose you, Manana!

376
00:15:44,041 --> 00:15:45,083
Wh-Why me?

377
00:15:45,166 --> 00:15:46,750
'Cause you're so good at it!

378
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,500
Uh... A-hem.

379
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:51,416
Kab-kabaddi. Kab-kabaddi.
Kab-kabaddi. Kab-kabaddi.

380
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,833
[MADOKA]
Just touch them and turn back.

381
00:15:57,666 --> 00:16:00,291
As soon as you stop struggling,
I can let you go.

382
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:01,375
[CHIO]
Hold the phone!

383
00:16:01,458 --> 00:16:03,250
This is not what
she described earlier!

384
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,125
This is good! Keep
trying to get away.

385
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:06,666
We'll continue to hold you
down until you give up.

386
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:08,250
I give up! Get off!

387
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,333
[CHIO]
She is not messing around!

388
00:16:10,416 --> 00:16:12,625
[GAME ANNOUNCER]
Manana is out!

389
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:14,875
So, there's no rush or anything,

390
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:17,208
but you never said how we're
supposed to end this game.

391
00:16:17,291 --> 00:16:18,708
That's a very good question.

392
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:19,958
Usually, it's timed

393
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:22,291
and players go out and
back in until it ends.

394
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,291
But we all have to get
to school eventually,

395
00:16:24,375 --> 00:16:25,625
so I think we should just play

396
00:16:25,708 --> 00:16:28,041
until one side is
completely eliminated.

397
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:30,166
[CHIO] Huh?! Wait!
Now it's them against me,

398
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,875
and if I get jumped, we lose?

399
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:34,583
I wanna be the raider
for our team next!

400
00:16:34,666 --> 00:16:37,250
[CHIO] So if Hosokawa touches
me and then blasts off,

401
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:40,708
we become members
of Awkward Tag Club?

402
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,958
I guess I'll try to catch her,
but I have to be cautious

403
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:45,791
or she'll end up touching me
when I'm not expecting it.

404
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:48,791
Whoa. "Touching me when
I'm not expecting it."

405
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:50,833
Kabaddi's deep!

406
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:52,916
I think I'm having
an "a-ha" moment.

407
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,625
Being in a club
no one knows exists

408
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:56,875
instead of the Tennis Club
might make my school life

409
00:16:56,958 --> 00:16:58,708
frickin' magical.

410
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:01,666
[CLASSMATE 4A]
It's nice to meet you!

411
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,666
[CLASSMATE 4B] I love the
first day of class! Don't you?

412
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,750
What clubs are you in
this year, Miyamo?

413
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,166
Oh, I'm in the Kabaddi Club!

414
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:09,333
--Kaba...
--D?

415
00:17:09,416 --> 00:17:11,166
[CLASSMATE 4C]
Awesome! Kabaddi, kabaddi!

416
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:12,875
--Oh, no, I'm scared!
--[CLASSMATE 4C] Tackle!

417
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:14,375
[laughing]

418
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:16,083
--You got me!
--[CLASSMATE 4C] I win...

419
00:17:16,166 --> 00:17:17,958
Stop making fun of kabaddi!

420
00:17:18,041 --> 00:17:20,500
Also, the one who chants
is the raider, idiot!

421
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,708
You don't chant when you
tackle someone! That's defense!

422
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:24,458
Um, he didn't mean it?

423
00:17:24,541 --> 00:17:26,083
[CLASSMATE 4C]
Out of my face, freak.

424
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:27,333
[CHIO]
That's a big old nope!

425
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:28,791
I don't need the drama!

426
00:17:28,875 --> 00:17:31,208
Impressive. Looks like she's
actually got some skills.

427
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:33,541
[gasping] I'm out of breath.

428
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:36,291
[CHIO] Ugh! No clue
how I got past her.

429
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:38,125
Does that mean I'm
the raider now?

430
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:40,083
What kind of animals
can handle this?

431
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:42,083
My stamina bar's depleted.

432
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:44,750
But I must not let
this become my fate.

433
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,208
[MADOKA]
What the...?

434
00:17:46,291 --> 00:17:48,000
[CHIO] My below-average life
depends on me taking this

435
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:51,000
weird, violent playground
game spin-off seriously.

436
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:53,125
But it's so hard.

437
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:55,541
Game brain, activate!

438
00:17:55,625 --> 00:18:00,083
I'll treat kabaddi like a
PvP game and bust some ass!

439
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:04,166
And now, everyone I touch
will turn into ticking bombs.

440
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,791
My mission, turn both
enemies into said bombs

441
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:08,625
and then escape
before they explode.

442
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:11,750
If captured, I'll be
tortured and killed!

443
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:12,958
I'll need to perform a spell

444
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:15,416
in order to activate
my special ability.

445
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,416
Kabaddi.

446
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,333
[CHIO]
Yes! It's working!

447
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:19,708
[CHIO]
Kabaddi, kabaddi...

448
00:18:19,791 --> 00:18:21,333
[MADOKA]
Careful, Yuki! Stay close.

449
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:22,833
Something's changed.

450
00:18:22,916 --> 00:18:24,583
I don't trust that girl.

451
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:27,041
[CHIO]
Kabaddi, kabaddi, kabaddi!

452
00:18:27,125 --> 00:18:29,041
[gasps]

453
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:30,583
[MADOKA] Her strong skills
don't hide the fact

454
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:33,833
that she's still a noob.
She's too deep in our territory!

455
00:18:33,916 --> 00:18:35,416
Even if she manages to touch us,

456
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:38,500
there's no way she'll be able
to escape once we capture her!

457
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,000
I've got her back!

458
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:42,708
Now! Run, Yuki! Tackle her

459
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:44,375
'Kay!

460
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,666
[CHIO]
When the enemy grabs you, twist!

461
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,625
It'll throw them off balance
and give you an advantage!

462
00:18:49,708 --> 00:18:52,875
Nice move, but I'm
not letting go!

463
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:56,041
[CHIO] Naturally, she's coming
straight for me with no tact.

464
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:58,416
Kabaddi!

465
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,791
I got a move for
that, too, biyotch!

466
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:01,666
Switch!

467
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:04,083
[YUKI yelps]

468
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,125
[gasping]

469
00:19:12,958 --> 00:19:15,000
Um, does this mean she won?

470
00:19:15,083 --> 00:19:16,333
Um...

471
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,500
[YUKI]
Okay! I think Miyamo's leaving!

472
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:20,625
Uh...

473
00:19:20,708 --> 00:19:22,916
So, Kushitori, can
you move your hand?

474
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:28,458
[CHIO]
Mission complete.

475
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:32,750
I tagged you both
and made it back.

476
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:35,250
I win. I'm outta here.

477
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,875
[MADOKA] No. First tell
me how you did that.

478
00:19:37,958 --> 00:19:40,750
So, um, about your hand?

479
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,666
I saw the twinkle in your eye
when you attacked Manana.

480
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,416
I recognized it and used
it to my advantage.

481
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:49,541
You're a sucker for the ladies.
Nothin' wrong with that.

482
00:19:49,625 --> 00:19:51,625
And then, when
Hosokawa was raiding,

483
00:19:51,708 --> 00:19:53,750
